</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9E8D87F23AD6EB451582AECC588D6F31" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="notes">
<paragraph id="85B73A8DDA8609D386A97BBBE0892256" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8611EC93AACAAE74AC787156AB3F8CBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="B6DEB157B8011F07A9B2530E09DC4857" class="Pezizomycetes" family="Helvellaceae" genus="Helvella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Helvella tianshanensis" order="Pezizales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tianshanensis">
<emphasis id="F66DBAB3DCBE43259C9CEF3AFD78FAE8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Helvella tianshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nested with 
<taxonomicName id="D465F83EC01F2C243D373269EE5AF33B" genus="H." lsidName="H. calycina" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="calycina">
<emphasis id="9C448E3C6076B17A00E57081C81708E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. calycina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E519742986C6554164425299BDFFE807" genus="H." lsidName="H. costifera" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="costifera">
<emphasis id="F4C9FECF317345B7416266137A9D5AEB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. costifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Clade 1 (
<figureCitation id="0795212150AC08F41874BD249868EDD0" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Bayesian phylogenetic tree of Helvella and Dissingia inferred from combined Hsp 90, ITS 2, LSU and TEF 1 dataset. Posterior probability values ≥ 0.90 (left) and bootstrap values ≥ 70 % (right) are indicated at nodes." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352437" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" tableDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure1">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). These three species are hardly separated by gross morphology and anatomic structures. 
<taxonomicName id="E9BFFB19F9EC3FF70CDF24FB84AB6640" class="Pezizomycetes" family="Helvellaceae" genus="Helvella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Helvella tianshanensis" order="Pezizales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tianshanensis">
<emphasis id="A5DFC46809E8302FCB9313C53C4759D5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Helvella tianshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="206045B75A396BF4EC747E0A97176276" genus="H." lsidName="H. calycina" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="calycina">
<emphasis id="D21B49DFF56AEA7B96A0045F7B75F261" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. calycina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 4 bp of Hsp90 (H022, epitype), 16 bp of ITS2 (HMAS 279704), 9 bp of LSU (H022) and 15 bp of TEF1 (H022); and it is different from 
<taxonomicName id="C600CA09E7BA977AE510CD1F9638D91F" genus="H." lsidName="H. costifera" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="costifera">
<emphasis id="E03269C55BC63F051ABF4E0744C84EBD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. costifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 3 bp of Hsp90 (H298, epitype), 12 bp of ITS2 (HMAS 187120), 11 bp of LSU (H131) and 13 bp of TEF1 (H131). The two specimens of the new species are identical in Hsp90 and ITS2.
</paragraph>
